  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat and boil a kettle</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-5 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1699442179460-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1699442179460-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1699442179460-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1699442179460-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1699442179460-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion is softening, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger </strong>and <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Bash your <strong>lemongrass</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>softer inner core</strong> finely</p><p>Remove the <strong>tough outer layers</strong> of the lemongrass and set aside for later</p><p>Slice <strong>half</strong> your<strong> red chilli[es]</strong> into rounds and finely chop the remaining</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1699442184118-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1699442184118-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1699442184118-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1699442184118-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1699442184118-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>,<strong> garlic</strong>, <strong>lemongrass</strong>, and<strong> chopped</strong> <strong>chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>diced chicken breast</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>cider vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to brown</p><p>While the chicken is browning, drain and rinse your <strong>green lentils</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1699442187554-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1699442187554-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1699442187554-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1699442187554-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1699442187554-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>creamed</strong> <strong>coconut</strong> (if required!), then dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and <strong>chopped creamed coconut </strong>in 500ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[650ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[850ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p><p>Once the chicken is starting to brown, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>rinsed lentils</strong> and <strong>coconut stock </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat, then once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for an initial 18-20 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1699442191846-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1699442191846-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1699442191846-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
